  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acute fluid collections is common in patients with severe acute pancreatitis (SAP). But the
      treatment for this is controversial. In this study, the investigators aim to evaluate the
      different effects of three different treatment protocols which is repeated aspiration,
      continuous catheter drainage and conservative treatment. The investigators suppose repeated
      aspiration could not only solve acute fluid collections, but also lower the rate of
      pancreatic infection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
